import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='population', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="engineers_per_capita", data=data, palette="viridis")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of engineers per capita across different states?", wrap=True)
    ax.legend(loc="upper right", title="States")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.ylabel('Number of Hurricanes')

    return plt;
